execute(responseStatusCallback, jsonObject)[source]¶

This method will be called to execute the functionality implemented in a command.

Parameters:

  • responseStatusCallback (function) – A callback function has to be passed, that will send status of command execution. This callback will be passed by the caller of execute().

  • jsonObject (json object) – A JSON object containing relevant data for a command.

Raises:

NotImplementedError – abstract class

printHello(responseStatusCallback, jsonObject)[source]¶

This method will be called to set speed for wheels.

Parameters:

  • responseStatusCallback (func) – A callback function has to be passed, that will send status of command execution back to the controller. This callback will be passed by the caller of execute().

  • jsonObject (dictionary) – A JSON object initially containing the command json, modified to include response information.
